#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:103
msgid "Paying twice for the same electricity"
msgstr "Pagar dos veces la misma electricidad"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:105
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On sunny hours the peninsula often produces more solar than the local"
" grid can absorb. That energy\n"
"    may go unused while other plants remain in the mix—so consumers can "
"pay for flexibility and system\n"
"    constraints twice over. It is measurable, costly, and largely "
"avoidable with better infrastructure\n"
"    and market design.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    En horas soleadas la península a menudo produce más solar de la que "
"la red local absorbe. Esa energía\n"
"    puede quedar sin usar mientras siguen otros tipos de generación: los "
"consumidores acaban pagando\n"
"    la flexibilidad y las restricciones del sistema dos veces. Es "
"medible, costoso y en buena parte\n"
"    evitable con mejor infraestructura y diseño de mercado.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:113
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What would help?</strong> Stronger grids and storage over "
"time, and price signals that reward\n"
"    using clean power when it is abundant. That reduces waste, eases "
"bills, and puts scarce clean\n"
"    generation to work—policy choices we already understand.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    <strong>¿Qué ayudaría?</strong> Redes y almacenamiento más robustos, "
"y señales de precio que premien\n"
"    usar energía limpia cuando abunda. Eso reduce desperdicio, alivia "
"facturas y pone a trabajar\n"
"    generación limpia escasa—decisiones de política que ya conocemos.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:122
msgid "City-sized picture"
msgstr "A escala de ciudad"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:124
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today’s unused solar total is in the ballpark of the daily "
"electricity of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> typical homes, using an illustrative "
"%(kwh)s kWh per home per day\n"
"    for scale (not a census count—see methodology).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El total de solar no utilizado hoy ronda el consumo diario de unas\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> viviendas típicas, con un valor "
"ilustrativo de %(kwh)s kWh por hogar y día\n"
"    para dar escala (no es un censo; ver metodología).\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:133
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr "Metodología"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:135
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Quarter-hourly unused solar (MWh) is derived from Red Eléctrica de "
"España (REE) data, processed in\n"
"    a separate pipeline and stored in this project’s database: each row "
"is keyed by date_day with\n"
"    qh_1_mwh through qh_100_mwh (15-minute buckets). Multiple rows for "
"the same day are summed\n"
"    bucket-wise before display.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    La energía solar no utilizada por cuartos de hora (MWh) procede de "
"datos de Red Eléctrica de España (REE),\n"
"    se procesa en una canalización aparte y se almacena en la base de "
"datos de este proyecto: cada fila va por\n"
"    date_day con columnas qh_1_mwh a qh_100_mwh (intervalos de 15 "
"minutos). Si hay varias filas el mismo día,\n"
"    se suman los cubos antes de mostrarlas.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:143
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars "
"(Europe/Madrid calendar day). Any slots\n"
"    beyond the first 96 are folded into the last hour of the day. Day "
"totals are the sum of all\n"
"    quarter-hour values. “So far this year” uses SUM(total_mwh) across "
"rows from 1 January through the\n"
"    selected date. The average “per hour” figure is the mean of the 24 "
"hourly bars (equivalently the\n"
"    day total divided by 24).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El gráfico agrega esos cuartos de hora en 24 barras horarias (día "
"natural Europa/Madrid). Los huecos\n"
"    más allá de los primeros 96 se incorporan a la última hora del día. "
"Los totales del día son la suma de\n"
"    todos los cuartos. “Lo que llevamos de año” usa SUM(total_mwh) entre "
"filas del 1 de enero hasta la fecha\n"
"    elegida. La media “por hora” es la media de las 24 barras (equivale a"
" total del día / 24).\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:152
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro amounts appear only when WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH is set; they "
"apply a simple illustrative rate\n"
"    × energy, not a market settlement—but they make clear that unused MWh"
" are not economically neutral.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Los importes en euros solo aparecen si WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH está "
"definido; aplican un tipo ilustrativo\n"
"    simple × energía, no un cierre de mercado—pero dejan claro que los "
"MWh no aprovechados no son neutrales en coste.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:157
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr "Analogía con hogares"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:159
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable illustrative kWh/day "
"figure to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale; replace or calibrate it when you publish official assumptions."
"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    La comparación con hogares usa un valor ilustrativo de kWh/día "
"configurable para dar una escala intuitiva;\n"
"    sustitúyelo o calíbralo cuando publiques supuestos oficiales.\n"
"    "

